Multisite XML-RPC
================================================================================

This plugin adds some Multisite-specific functions to WordPress' XML-RPC interface.
The functions are:

Create Blog (ms.CreateBlog)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Creates a new blog calling wpmu_create_blog (documentation at
http://codex.wordpress.org/WPMU_Functions/wpmu_create_blog).

Like other WordPress' XML-RPC functions, expects an array with user, password and
function parameters (the parameters of wpmu_create_blog). Ex:

array(
	'admin',
	'password',
	array(
		'example.com',
		'path',
		'Blog Title',
		user_id,
	)
);

This implementation differs from the codex documented one: You can
use an e-mail instead of user id. If so, a new user will be created (if not exists)
or the user_id of the e-mail owner will be used.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Get Blog Id
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Returns the blog_id of given domain and path in a XML-RPC request.
Expects an array with user, password and function parameters. The parameters are:
$domain  The blog domain
$path    The blog path
Ex:

array(
	'admin',
	'password',
	array(
		'example.com',
		'path'
	)
);
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Update Archived
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Updates the archived status of a blog calling WP's update_archived function
(documentation at http://codex.wordpress.org/WPMU_Functions/update_archived)

This function expects an array with user, password and function parameters
(the parameters of updated_archived). Ex:

array(
	'admin',
	'password',
	array(2, 1)
);
